title: The Interrupting GOD
description:
Jeff P, Jess P, & Luke T discuss the problem with God asking Abraham to sacrifice Isaac.  Prompted by a previous Randos discussion between Nathan and Julian, titled "Honest Objections".   Nathan asked some simple and difficult questions.  Does a religion where God asks a man to sacrifice his son set a bad precedent?  Could God ask you to kill your mother?

God doesn't just ask Abraham to kill his son, but he also interrupts him as he raises the knife and provides a substitute.
